MBOMBELA &#8211; &#8220;Even though I am having a great time overseas, my heart still belongs to the Lowveld. To come back here and start a business is definitely not out of the question,&#8221; acclaimed chef Anmar Wilding told Lowvelder a year ago. Originally from the city, she was presenting a master class in macaron and mini-meringue making in White River, during a visit from the United Kingdom (UK) at the time. Because of a new immigration-skills charge to be introduced in April 2017, she has been forced to move back to South Africa a little sooner than she had anticipated.